all of canvas, she guessed that multifarious and antithetical points to propositions of truth were all there was.\par }\pard \widctlpar\nooverflow\faroman\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs22      A child, even this one, was a sensitive creature whom she, an adult, needed to emphasize certain points to while tiptoeing away from others.  But, she argued in solitary inward dialogues within herself, which she found to be the most engaging form of companionship, that did not necessarily mean that her quiet tiptoeing prevarications were lies.\par     With words as the most viable means of projecting a given concept of one mind onto another and with them having to permeate the dense grey matter, unchanged, through the hard surface of experience and preference, it was a wonder that misunderstandings did not rule fully in all human concerns.  A small lie here and there in place of misunderstood truth, she argued, was the expedient of presidents and kings.  Even this Texan hick, George Jr., who seemed to her as abhorrent as a president was likely to become, was marginally justified in misleading the American populace the way she had been forced to deviate from truth for the sake of her son.  The apocryphal president could not have averred his wish to contrive a war against any rogue state for any random reason even though that was his intention.  He could not have declared that North Korea, the desired bombing target for setting this example of what hegemony could do, had been spared from war by Seoul\rquote s proximity to the DMZ and that Iraq had been chosen to be the favored ersatz.  He needed an imminent threat to sell his war:  these elusive weapons of mass destruction, which could always be argued as \ldblquote out there,\rdblquote  present but obscure.\par      Just as she could not have admitted to Nathaniel that Rick had been the favored one all along, now she was still reluctant to admit to herself that on that night when she brought him home she had fallen into su